    <p>The In­sult (2017, PG13)</p>
    <p>In Beirut, an ar­gu­ment over ren­o­va­tions lands Toni, a Le­banese Chris­tian, and Yasser, a Pales­tinian refugee, in court. The me­dia cir­cus sur­round­ing the case puts Le­banon through a so­cial ex­plo­sion, forc­ing Toni and Yasser to re­con­sider their lives and prej­u­dices. This work was a best for­eign lan­guage film nom­i­nee at the Os­cars in 2018.</p>
    <p>PRICE: $10 for a 48-hour rental pe­riod INFO: str.sg/JBas</p>
    <p>Beasts Claw­ing At Straws (2020, NC16)</p>
    <p>In this star-stud­ded South Korean crime thriller, eight strangers who are fi­nan­cially strapped be­come in­volved af­ter a bag of money is found in a sauna by a strug­gling restau­rant owner who cares for his sick mother. Soon, a dead body turns up. Other char­ac­ters in­clude a cus­toms of­fi­cer, whose girl­friend runs off with money he bor­rowed from a loan shark, and a wo­man with an abu­sive hus­band and a dead-end job as a bar host­ess. WHERE: The Pro­jec­tor, Level 5, Golden Mile Tower, 6001 Beach Road</p>
    <p>MRT: Ni­coll High­way WHEN: Tue, 7.30pm AD­MIS­SION: $13.50</p>
    <p>INFO: str.sg/JBae</p>


